-- China shares end down 0.2 pct on dashed stimulus hopes
-- 
-- Wed May 30, 2012 8:07am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2012/05/30/us-markets-china-stocks-idUSBRE84T08U20120530

 

 SHANGHAI  (Reuters) - Chinese shares ended down 0.2 percent on Wednesday, dragged down by media reports which dampened market hopes that Beijing is considering another massive stimulus program. 
 The Shanghai Composite Index  .SSEC  finished at 2,384.7 points, after rising 1.2 percent on Tuesday. (Reporting by Chen Yixin and  Pete Sweeney ; Editing by Jacqueline Wong)